This paper deals with the design of reversible circuits, which is a topic in the subfield of computer engineering known as reversible computing. The paper also discusses theoretical results related to reversible circuits, which suggests that it may belong to the subfield of theoretical computer science (cs.TH). However, the focus of the paper is on designing parity preserving reversible circuits, which suggests that it may belong to the subfield of electronic design automation (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of computer architecture (cs.AR), logic in computer science (cs.LO), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and programming languages (cs.PL) due to its focus on circuit design and theoretical results.
